The paper proposes a method for interpreting the decision-making process of deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves aligning visual concepts with net-units and inferring concepts hierarchically, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the explanation of net layer structure, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
